  "ciliary_role": "Inhibits beta-catenin-mediated transcriptio l activation by competing with Tcf/Lef. Cby1 is required for recruitment of Arl13b to the primary cilium. Promotes Ahi1 localisation to the centriole and is probably important for assembly and function of transition zone components (25103236). Cby1 may associate with membranes to promote the recruitment of FAM92 proteins for their higher-order assembly and subsequent membrane remodelling to promote ciliogenesis (27528616). Because of its proximity to the membrane vesicle, it is possible that Cby proteins may be involved in targeting and/or attachmentof the vesicles to the centriole, controlling intraflagellar transport and protein sorting of the ciliary membrane (22911743).",
